Enabler 2 — The right people. Three roles matter, and you need all three:

An executive sponsor who owns the value, not just the budget. Someone at leadership level who will reallocate time saved into actual business outcomes, because AI that saves time doesn't create value until the time is redeployed.
Functional champions — one per area where AI is deployed. The finance manager's curious 2IC, the sales leader's most adaptable rep. They become the local expert and the first line of support. Without them, adoption stalls.
